# README.me
# Purpose: Entry point for all Android implementation work on Book A Dink.
#          Defines what each file in this directory governs, which file is
#          authoritative for each topic, how to resolve conflicts, and the
#          recommended read order before writing any Android code.
# Scope: android_build/ directory

---

## WHAT IS THIS DIRECTORY

`android_build/` is the source of truth for building the Book A Dink Android app.
It defines behaviour, constraints, architecture, and test requirements derived from
the live iOS product and Supabase backend.

These files are enforceable contracts, not suggestions. If a rule conflicts with
an assumption made during implementation, the rule wins.

These files do NOT contain platform-specific code. They define what must be built,
not how to write Kotlin or Compose syntax.

---

## FILE DIRECTORY

### Guardrail Files (behaviour and rules)

| File | Governs | Authoritative For |
|---|---|---|
| `system_contracts.me` | Core product lifecycle rules | Booking state machine, payment flow, credit rules, waitlist protocol, cancellation logic, subscription entitlements |
| `backend_authority.me` | Server-enforced constraints | What is never trusted from clients, RLS policies, Edge Function responsibilities, schema constraints |
| `data_contracts.me` | Entity structures and enums | Table schemas, required query columns, enum values, UUID/date/currency handling rules |
| `client_guardrails.me` | Client DO/DO NOT rules | What iOS and Android can and cannot do; layout, network, auth, admin, chat constraints |
| `ux_parity.me` | Cross-platform UX consistency | CTA labels, booking state display, payment badges, error messages, menu order, review and chat UX |
| `platform_adaptation.me` | iOS vs Android equivalents | Stripe SDK mapping, APNsв†’FCM, deep links, location, in-app browser, storage, image loading |
| `edge_cases.me` | Failure handling | Race conditions, partial states, retry logic, connectivity failures, all known production failure modes |

### Planning Files (Android-specific)

| File | Governs | Authoritative For |
|---|---|---|
| `README.me` *(this file)* | Directory orientation | Read order, conflict resolution, file responsibilities |
| `android_v1_scope.me` | What to build | Included features, excluded features, priorities, dependencies, blockers |
| `android_architecture.me` | How to structure the app | Layers, repositories, state management, module boundaries, backend interaction rules |
| `android_test_matrix.me` | How to validate it | Parity test cases, edge case coverage, failure path tests, regression targets |

