## CONFLICT RESOLUTION ORDER

If two files appear to say different things about the same behaviour, resolve in this order:

1. **`system_contracts.me`** вЂ” wins for all product lifecycle behaviour
2. **`backend_authority.me`** вЂ” wins for all server-side enforcement decisions
3. **`data_contracts.me`** вЂ” wins for all schema and data format questions
4. **`client_guardrails.me`** вЂ” wins for all client-side restrictions
5. **`ux_parity.me`** вЂ” wins for all display and copy decisions
6. **`platform_adaptation.me`** вЂ” wins for Android-specific implementation choices
7. **`edge_cases.me`** вЂ” wins for failure handling specifics
8. **`android_v1_scope.me`** вЂ” wins for what is in/out of scope for v1
9. **`android_architecture.me`** вЂ” wins for structural and layering decisions
10. **`android_test_matrix.me`** вЂ” wins for test coverage requirements

If a conflict cannot be resolved by this order, the iOS production behaviour is the
tiebreaker вЂ” the Android app must match what is live on iOS unless explicitly scoped out.

