## RECOMMENDED READ ORDER

Read these files in order before writing any Android code:

1. `README.me` (this file) вЂ” orientation
2. `android_v1_scope.me` вЂ” know what you are building
3. `system_contracts.me` вЂ” understand the product rules
4. `data_contracts.me` вЂ” understand the data structures
5. `backend_authority.me` вЂ” understand what the server enforces
6. `client_guardrails.me` вЂ” understand client constraints
7. `platform_adaptation.me` вЂ” understand iOS в†’ Android mappings
8. `ux_parity.me` вЂ” understand required UX behaviour
9. `edge_cases.me` вЂ” understand what can go wrong
10. `android_architecture.me` вЂ” design the app structure
11. `android_test_matrix.me` вЂ” plan validation

Do not start implementing a feature until you have read the file that governs it.
Do not invent behaviour for a missing case вЂ” check the iOS app or ask.

